javax.swing.plaf.nimbus

Class NimbusStyle.Values

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.swing.plaf.nimbus.NimbusStyle.Values
  • Enclosing class:
    NimbusStyle

    private static final class NimbusStyle.Values
extends Object
    Essentially a struct of data for a style. A default instance of this class is used by NimbusStyle. Additional instances exist for each component that has overrides.

    • Field Detail

      • stateTypes

        State[] stateTypes
        The list of State types. A State represents a type of state, such as Enabled, Default, WindowFocused, etc. These can be custom states.

      • states

        NimbusStyle.RuntimeState[] states
        The list of actual runtime state representations. These can represent things such as Enabled + Focused. Thus, they differ from States in that they contain several states together, and have associated properties, data, etc.

      • contentMargins

        Insets contentMargins
        The content margins for this region.

      • defaults

        UIDefaults defaults
        Defaults on the region/component level.

      • cache

        Map<NimbusStyle.CacheKey,Object> cache
        Simple cache. After a value has been looked up, it is stored in this cache for later retrieval. The key is a concatenation of the property being looked up, two dollar signs, and the extended state. So for example: foo.bar$$2353
